    {# ══════ PRELIMS DATA ══════ #}
    <div class="pq-section" id="prelims-data">
      <h2 class="pq-section-head">Prelims — Subject-wise Question Count (2019-2024)</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-size:var(--text-xs);margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">Verified counts from official UPSC CSE Prelims GS Paper 1. Classification based on primary theme.</p>

      <div class="pyq-table-wrap" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">
        <table class="pyq-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Subject</th><th>2019</th><th>2020</th><th>2021</th><th>2022</th><th>2023</th><th>2024</th><th>Avg</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Current Affairs</td><td>17</td><td>19</td><td>14</td><td>13</td><td>16</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">20</td><td><strong>16.5</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Environment & Ecology</td><td>14</td><td>11</td><td>15</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">27</td><td>13</td><td>10</td><td><strong>15.0</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Economy</td><td>16</td><td>14</td><td>15</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">17</td><td>14</td><td>15</td><td><strong>15.2</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Polity & Governance</td><td>15</td><td>15</td><td>14</td><td>8</td><td>15</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">18</td><td><strong>14.2</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>History & Culture</td><td>17</td><td>19</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">20</td><td>9</td><td>14</td><td>9</td><td><strong>14.7</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Geography</td><td>12</td><td>12</td><td>10</td><td>12</td><td>16</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">19</td><td><strong>13.5</strong></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Science & Technology</td><td>9</td><td>10</td><td>12</td><td class="pyq-table__highlight">14</td><td>12</td><td>9</td><td><strong>11.2</strong></td></tr>
          </tbody>
          <caption>Sources: SuperKalam PYQ analysis (2019-2023), PW OnlyIAS (2024). Highlighted = highest for that year.</caption>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="pyq-insight"><strong>Key insight:</strong> No single subject dominates every year. Environment spiked to 27 in 2022, Geography surged to 19 in 2024, History hit 20 in 2021. UPSC deliberately rotates emphasis — you cannot afford to skip any subject.</div>
      <div class="pyq-insight"><strong>Current Affairs:</strong> Averaged ~16.5 standalone, but true exposure is 30-40% when CA-linked questions in every subject are counted.</div>
    </div>

    {# ══════ CUTOFFS ══════ #}
    <div class="pq-section" id="cutoff">
      <h2 class="pq-section-head">Prelims Cutoff Trends — General Category</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--color-text-muted);font-size:var(--text-xs);margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">Minimum qualifying marks (out of 200) to clear Prelims.</p>

      <div class="pyq-table-wrap" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-4);">
        <table class="pyq-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Year</th><th>2019</th><th>2020</th><th>2021</th><th>2022</th><th>2023</th><th>2024</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Cutoff (General)</td><td>98.00</td><td>92.51</td><td>87.54</td><td>88.22</td><td class="pyq-table__low">75.41</td><td>87.98</td></tr>
            <tr><td>As % of 200</td><td>49.0%</td><td>46.3%</td><td>43.8%</td><td>44.1%</td><td class="pyq-table__low">37.7%</td><td>44.0%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
          <caption>Source: UPSC official cutoff notifications. 2023 dipped sharply — attributed to harder paper.</caption>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="pyq-insight"><strong>What this means:</strong> You need ~90-100 marks (45-50%) in a normal year. With -0.66 marking, answering 75 correctly out of 85 attempted is safe. The 2023 dip shows cutoff adjusts for difficulty — don't panic on a hard paper.</div>
    </div>

